1.2 Normalisation & Exploratory analysis

1.2.0.1 By samples

assay(dds, "counts.norm.VST") = as.data.frame(assay(varianceStabilizingTransformation(dds,blind=T)),check.names=F)

par(mfrow=c(1,3))
boxplot(log10(as.matrix(assay(dds, "counts")+1)),ylab=expression('Log'[10]~'Read counts'),las=2,main="Raw counts filtered")
boxplot(log10(as.matrix(assay(dds, "counts.norm")+1)),ylab=expression('Log'[10]~'Read counts'),las=2,main="Median ratio")
boxplot(log10(as.matrix(assay(dds, "counts.norm.VST")+1)),ylab=expression('Log'[10]~'Read counts'),las=2,main="VST")

For RNA-seq data, as the mean count value increases, the variance increases. There is a strong almost linear relationship as seen in the figures. The statistical methods such as PCA expects similar variance across the range of mean values. If not, the higher variance genes will contribute more than the lower variance genes. Such data is said to be heteroscedastic and needs to be corrected. Correction using log transformation (with pseudocount) now inflates the contribution of the low variance genes. To obtain similar variance across the whole range of mean values, DESeq2 offers two methods VST (variance stabilising transformation) and RLOG (regularised log transformation).

As the name suggests, VST transformation stabilizes variance across the whole range of count values. VST is recommended for clustering or visualisation. It is not intended for differential gene expression. If the size factors vary dramatically between samples, then RLOG transformation is recommended.

normalized_data <- rowSums(normalized_counts>0)

1.2.1 Density

RNA_count_ratio1_ID <- as.data.frame(normalized_counts)
RNA_count_ratio1_ID$fid <- rownames(RNA_count_ratio1_ID)

palette4 = c("#dd5129", "#0f7ba2", "#43b284", "#fab255")  #MetBrewer palette egypt

plot_sample_density_log <- function(exp, title) {
  exp_long <- exp %>% pivot_longer(!fid, values_to = 'value', names_to = 'id')
  exp_long$Condition <- metadata2$Condition[match(exp_long$id, metadata2$Sample)]
  exp_long$Condition <- factor(exp_long$Condition, levels = unique(exp_long$Condition))
  exp_long %>%
    #filter(donor == 'B') %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = value, color = Condition)) +
      geom_density(na.rm = T, bw = 'sj') +
      # scale_x_continuous(trans='log2') +
      scale_color_manual(values = c(palette4)) +
      theme(legend.position = "below") +
      ggtitle(title) +
      scale_x_log10(breaks = trans_breaks("log10", function(x) 10^x),
              labels = trans_format("log10", math_format(10^.x))) 
}

p.hist.ratio1 <- plot_sample_density_log(RNA_count_ratio1_ID, "Ratios 1")
p.hist.ratio1

library(UpSetR)
library(ComplexUpset)
library(ggplot2)
library(patchwork)
library(ggpubr)



### Chronics comparison

df_resMale$padj[is.na(df_resMale$padj)] <- 1

human <- list(
  `IS logFC < 0` = rownames(df_resSex[df_resSex$padj < 0.05 & df_resSex$log2FoldChange < 0,] ),
  `IS logFC > 0` = rownames(df_resSex[df_resSex$padj < 0.05 & df_resSex$log2FoldChange > 0,] ),
  
  `IM logFC < 0` = rownames(df_resMale[df_resMale$padj < 0.05 & df_resMale$log2FoldChange < 0,] ),
  `IM logFC > 0` = rownames(df_resMale[df_resMale$padj < 0.05 & df_resMale$log2FoldChange > 0,] ),
  
  `IF logFC < 0` = rownames(df_resFemale[df_resFemale$padj < 0.05 & df_resFemale$log2FoldChange < 0,] ),
  `IF logFC > 0` = rownames(df_resFemale[df_resFemale$padj < 0.05 & df_resFemale$log2FoldChange > 0,] )
)

human <- fromList(human)



fig_upset <- ComplexUpset::upset(
  human,
  colnames(human),
  name = 'Intersections between comparisons',
  width_ratio = 0.2,
  sort_sets = F,
  sort_intersections_by=c('degree',"cardinality"),
  stripes=c( 'white','#e0e0e0'),
  # group_by = "degree",
  themes = upset_modify_themes(list(
    'intersections_matrix' = theme(text = element_text(size = 12), axis.text.y =
                                     element_text(size = 12)),
    'overall_sizes' = theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0))
  )),
  matrix = (
    intersection_matrix(geom = geom_point(shape = 'circle filled', size = 3))
    + scale_color_manual(
      values = c(
        "IS logFC < 0" = "#88A0DC",
        "IS logFC > 0" = "#88A0DC",
        "IM logFC < 0" = "#d5a5cf",
        "IM logFC > 0" = "#d5a5cf",
        "IF logFC < 0" = "#ef8737",
        "IF logFC > 0" = "#ef8737"
      )
      # guide=guide_legend(override.aes=list(shape='circle'))
    )
  ),
  queries = list(
    upset_query(set = "IS logFC < 0", fill = "#88A0DC"),
    upset_query(set = "IS logFC > 0", fill = "#88A0DC"),
    upset_query(set = "IM logFC < 0", fill = "#d5a5cf"),
    upset_query(set = "IM logFC > 0", fill = "#d5a5cf"),
    upset_query(set = 'IF logFC < 0', fill = "#ef8737"),
    upset_query(set = 'IF logFC > 0', fill = "#ef8737")
  )
)
